<font color="#FF0000">THANKS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Feb 21 15:02:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I Have a bumper sticker that states, &quot; If you (HEART) your <br>
freedom, Thank a veteran !&quot;. It was given to me at a <br>
&quot;POW/MIA Recognician Day&quot; at Fort Devins, Mass. in Oct.'88.<br>
It is still on my bumper altough it is weathered badly.<br>
A few months ago a car kept riding the bumper of the car in<br>
the lane beside me. after a few minutes I slowed to allow<br>
 the lead car to change lanes before someone had an accident.<br>
The driver of the offending car pulled even with me and<br>
started trying to get my attention. When he had it, he held<br>
up a spirel notebook on which he had written &quot;THANK YOU for<br>
my Freedom.&quot;<br>
At first I didn't realize the reason, but it soon dawned.<br>
Eight years and I got an unexpected &quot;THANK YOU&quot;! Unexpected<br>
because the driver was a clean-cut,well-dressed, young <br>
businessman and I had longer hair, a beard, and working <br>
class clothing. Thanks. It almost made it worth my cost.<br>
THANKS to ALL YOU VETERANS and thanks for this site.     
<p><code>-- b2x4x93  (William T. (REB) Marthers) </code><p>


